- Context: This is the second page of the COSHH Assessment Guide and outlines the responsibilities, step-by-step approach, and glossary.
- Text: 4. Responsibilities
It is the responsibility of the manager to ensure that a suitable and sufficient COSHH
assessment is carried out.
5. Step-by-Step Approach
5.1 Initial Screening
Use information from the MSDS to complete the initial screening. Refer to Appendix 1 for
a sample.
5.2 Conduct the COSHH Assessment
Refer to Appendix 2 for a sample COSHH assessment format.
5.3 Document the Findings
Document the findings of the COSHH assessment, including the identified hazards, risks,
and control measures.
5.4 Review the COSHH Assessment
Review the COSHH assessment periodically, or when there are significant changes in the
workplace.
6. Glossary
COSHH: Control of Substances Hazardous to Health.
MSDS: Material Safety Data Sheet.
Risk: The likelihood of harm occurring from exposure to a hazard.
Hazard: A substance, activity, or condition that has the potential to cause harm.
Control Measures: Actions taken to reduce the risk of exposure to a hazard.
