- Context: This page outlines Health and Safety regulations, common challenges, continuous improvement strategies, and what sets the Operational Assurance Group apart. It includes information about the Health and Safety at Work etc. Act 1974 (HSWA) and the Management of Health and Safety at Work Regulations 1999 (MHSWR).
- Text: Health and Safety at Work etc. Act 1974 (HSWA)
•	Duty to protect employees and others

Management of Health and Safety at Work Regulations 1999 (MHSWR)
0	Requires risk assessment and control measures

Supporting HSE Guidance
•	HSG97: A Step by Step Guide to COSHH Assessment
•	EH40: Workplace Exposure Limits
•	INDG136: COSHH Brief Guide

10. Common Challenges
•	Over-reliance on generic assessments
•	Failure to use SDS effectively
•	Poor communication of controls
•	Overuse of PPE instead of higher-level controls
•	Lack of review and updates

11. Continuous Improvement
•	Regular review of assessments
•	Monitoring exposure levels
•	Workforce feedback
•	Incident and near-miss learning

